{"v":1,"id":"ocE6yhZjB8jmi1tnJaUZ","createdAt":"2026-06-16T13:31:06.855Z","app":{"name":"AxiVale","version":"0.5.0"},"kind":"response","title":"I'll pull last night's runs and identify the commander.","turns":[{"agentText":"\n\nI'll pull last night's runs and identify the commander.\n\nSingle raid last night, commanded by Prez Ashton. Let me pull the run detail and squad stats.\n\nOne raid last night (25 fights, 16–9), tagged by Prez Ashton on Firebrand. To set a baseline I'll pull their recent commanding history.\n\nPrez Ashton led three nights in the last month (Jun 1, Jun 8, Jun 15). Pulling the two prior to build the trend.\n\n# Kills still flow, but the squad is dying on the floor — Prez Ashton's third straight slide\n\nPrez Ashton tagged up for one raid last night (Jun 15, gw2eww/fight-reports): 25 fights, **16–9**, squad ~34 vs ~43 enemies. The damage and pressure are still there — 459 enemy kills, second-best of his three June nights — but squad survivability has eroded for the third raid running, and last night was the worst of the set. No runs were skipped; baseline is his Jun 1 and Jun 8 nights.\n\nThe clean read is win rate falling while a larger share of your own downs bleed out into deaths — the two lines are crossing the wrong way.\n\n{{figure}}\n\nAcross his three nights the kills hold up; it's the squad floor that's collapsing:\n\n| Night | Fights | W–L | K/D | Squad downs | Squad deaths | Downs that died |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Jun 1 | 23 | 21–2 | 6.8 | 191 | 71 | 37% |\n| Jun 8 | 27 | 20–7 | 2.3 | 365 | 173 | 47% |\n| Jun 15 | 25 | 16–9 | 2.3 | 382 | **201** | **53%** |\n\nJun 1 was a farm night (91% win, soft matchup). Strip the outlier and the trend is still clear: deaths climbed 71 → 173 → 201, and the down-to-death conversion worsened every raid. Last night over **half** of all squad downs turned into deaths — a rally/peel problem, not a damage problem.\n\n**Strengths to keep**\n- **Damage is not the issue.** BreakN (Berserker) 12.0M and Brotalist (Berserker) 9.6M led a backline that still put 685 downs on the enemy — squad output is healthy.\n- **Boon-strip/corrupt is heavily stacked.** Hostile Pudding 1,400 strips, Wisdom 1,153, undiee 1,071, General Moo 895 — plenty of pressure to break enemy stability and set up spikes.\n- **Stays in the fight.** 25 engagements at roughly even numbers (34 vs 43) — he's not ducking contact.\n\n**Coaching points**\n- **Peel/rally is the bottleneck.** 53% of downs died last night vs 37% on Jun 1. Call dedicated peels on downs and slow the re-push so Druid/Specter (Arx 8.1M heal, Tysun 3.7M) can land cleave-rezzes before the body is lost.\n- **Win rate is sliding (91→74→64%) at even odds, not while outnumbered.** Avg enemies were *fewer* last night than Jun 8 (43 vs 54) yet losses rose — that points to overcommitting pushes or stability gaps on the re-engage, not getting blobbed.\n- **Tighten the reset cadence.** With deaths front-loaded into losses, call harder disengages after a bad initiation rather than feeding a second push into the same spot.\n- **Watch squad-size sustain.** He ran a bigger squad (34) on this slide than on his clean Jun 1 night (29); confirm enough heal/cleanse bodies are spread per subgroup as the squad grows.\n\nDouble down on the aggressive target-calling and strip pressure — that's generating the kills. The one habit to change: stop trading downs for deaths. Slow the re-push and call peels, and a 16–9 night turns back into a 20+ win night without changing a single build.","filedAt":"6:26 AM","tools":[{"name":"axibridge_runs_list"},{"name":"axibridge_commander_stats","display":{"kind":"table","data":{"title":"Commanders","columns":[{"key":"account","label":"Commander"},{"key":"fightsLed","label":"Fights led"},{"key":"wins","label":"W"},{"key":"losses","label":"L"},{"key":"kdr","label":"KDR"},{"key":"deaths","label":"Deaths"}],"rows":[{"account":"harasho.4281","profession":"Troubadour","runs":19,"fightsLed":314,"wins":196,"losses":118